{
  "text": "( Fig. 2, E and F) . This was not caused by the persistence of radio-resistant skin DCs expressing lower CD11c levels, including Langerhans cells, the latter of which have been shown to resist high-dose irradiation [CITATION_1] . Thus, upon IMQ treatment, Il15ra \ue032/\ue032 -Cd11cDtr chimeras receiving DT showed an inflammatory skin response similar to that seen in control chimeras receiving PBS (Fig. 2 G) . Moreover, Langerin-Dtr (LangDtr) animals treated with DT were indistinguishable from PBS-treated LangDtr (Fig. 2 H) , suggesting that Langerhans cells were not implicated in IMQ-mediated psoriasiform skin pathology, neither in the IL-15-induced inflammation nor in the IL-15R\ue061-mediated dampening of disease.",
